<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf662927f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3308"><num value="3308">§ 3308.</num><heading> Examinations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to inspections required by <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s3307">section 3307 of this title</ref>, the Secretary shall examine or have examined—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6629280-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3308/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> each vessel subject to inspection at proper times to ensure compliance with law and regulations; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6629281-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3308/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><chapeau> crewmember accommodations on each vessel subject to inspection at least once a month or when the vessel enters United States ports to ensure that the accommodations are—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idf6629282-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3308/2/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> of the size required by law and regulations;</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idf6629283-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3308/2/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> properly ventilated and in a clean and sanitary condition; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idf6629284-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3308/2/C"><num value="C">(C)</num><content> equipped with proper plumbing and mechanical appliances required by law and regulations, and the appliances are in good working condition.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf6629285-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/514">97 Stat. 514</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/104/324/tVI/s603/c">Pub. L. 104–324, title VI, § 603(c)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-19">Oct. 19, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3930">110 Stat. 3930</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
